latestIgtvVideos.caption:
● In the past 10 years, tourism in Himachal has increased to ​68.17%​. In the year 2018, 160.94 lakh​ Indian and ​3.56 lakh f​ oreign tourists visited the state
● Tourism sector contributes to ​6.6%​ of the states GDP which is quite remarkable
● Beautiful streams, serene environment, hospitable people and marketing of the state in
print and electronic media are some of the reasons that are leading to continuous growth
in tourism in the state
● According to ​UNWTO​, ​Sustainable tourism meets the needs of present-day tourists
and host regions while protecting and enhancing opportunities for the future
● We have successfully collected 6,00,000 kgs of non-biodegradable waste from the remote villages and hamlets of the state where tourism is growing with every passing day
● According to Havard, in India more than 80% of collected waste is currently disposed of in open dumpsites ​or substandard landfills, with little or no environmental controls
● Collected waste has to be managed properly because if ​waste is not managed properly it will lead to local flooding, as well as air and water pollution

latestPosts.caption:
The mountains deserve better from us.

Every plastic bottle tossed on a trail, every wrapper left behind—it all adds up, and not in a good way.

This winter, as you pack your bags for a holiday, pack your responsibility too. Carry reusable bottles, bring back your trash, and remind others to do the same. Let’s make mindful tourism the norm.

It’s simple: Love the mountains? Don’t litter.

PS. A huge shoutout to every local resident, NGO, and volunteer working tirelessly to protect the mountains. Let’s support their efforts. 

@pradeep_sangwan_

#CleanMountains #ResponsibleTourism #SustainableTravel #responsiblecitizen #sustainableTourism #WinterVacation 

[Clean Mountains, Sustainable Travel, Responsible Tourism, Winter Vacations, Tourism in India]

latestPosts.caption:
Some of the highlights:
 

Himalayan districts in 13 Himalayan states & 148 districts. Not even a single district can claim 100% waste management ecosystem 

b) Identification of communities which are forthcoming to the scientific waste management implementation ideas. 

c) Tourism centric districts should be the the priority & An assessment is required in terms of what all recycling facilities do we have in all these Himalayan districts 

d) A missing puzzle which is C & D + textile waste disposal & recycling in the Himalayas 

e) We will convert from Climate tourist to climate refugees within no time. Happening knowingly or unknowingly 

f) Limited number trek routes which has complete waste management ecosystem & conservation of stings along the way or neighbouring villages 

A thought-provoking panel discussion on "Solid and Legacy Waste Management in Hilly Regions with a Climate Lens" at Parvat Manthan, organized by National Institute of Urban Affairs (NIUA)

latestPosts.caption:
This International Mountain Day, we pause to reflect on the critical role mountains play in our lives and the urgent need to protect them. Mountains provide us with freshwater, biodiversity, and cultural heritage—yet they are under threat. It’s time to come together and take action to reduce our footprints. Let’s unlearn the habits of overconsumption and adopt mindful, sustainable choices that respect the environment.

Mountains are more than majestic landscapes—they are a source of life. Together, we can safeguard these natural treasures for the well-being of future generations. 🌄🌱

 #InternationalMountainDay #ProtectMountains #SustainableLiving
#healinghimalayas
Cozy and cold morning. Going to work is 💚❄️🥶

A Big Step for a Cleaner Himalayas! 

We’re thrilled to announce our partnership with the State Rural Development Department of Himachal Pradesh to enhance waste management in rural and eco-sensitive areas. Together, the aim is to empower communities with sustainable practices like segregation, recycling, and eco-friendly waste disposal.

This collaboration strengthens our mission to protect the fragile Himalayan ecosystem and promote responsible living in these beautiful regions.

Here’s to creating scalable, sustainable solutions that benefit people of Himalayas and the planet. 

#HealingHimalayas #WasteManagement #SustainableLiving #EcoFriendly #ResponsibleTourism #Himalayas

latestPosts.caption:
Happy Mother’s Day 💚💚

I know it’s not Mother’s Day but I am still posting it. 

हिमालय जैसी मेरी माँ हमेशा मुझे बिना बताए बहुत कुछ सिखाती हैं । बचपन से ही मैं घर से बाहर रहा हूँ तो कहीं ना कहीं वो दिन प्रतिदिन का प्यार और गुस्सा कभी मिला नहीं 

हिमालय की सेवा करते करते पिछले 10 साल कैसे गुजरे ये भी पता नहीं चला । पर पिछले कुछ वर्सो से ऐसा महसूस होने लगा की कुछ कमी हैं और जैसे ही घर आता हूँ वो पूरी हो जाती हैं। मुझे याद हैं कुछ साल पहले जब मैं किन्नौर में था तो ये एहसास हुआ की देश की सेवा करने के लिए माँ का प्यार कितना जरूरी हैं । हालाकि मुझे ये भी एहसास हुआ की मैं कितना खुदगर्ज हूँ । पर मेरी माँ ये सब समझती हैं उसे सबकुछ क्यो समझ आजाता हैं यही सोच कर ये लिख रहा हूँ 

स्वार्थ भरी इस दुनिया में जब आप नकारात्मक हो जाते हैं तब माँ के सिर्फ़ साये भर से सकारात्मक हो जाना माँ के प्यार का प्रतिबिंब हैं । दुनिया भर में सबसे बड़ी प्रेरणा स्रोत अगर कोई हैं तो वो माँ हैं ।

माँ के साथ बिताए पल बहुत कीमती होते हैं क्योंकि वो प्यार, सहजता, सकारात्मकता केवल वही मिलता हैं और उसी सोच को आप दुनिया तक ले जाते हैं । दुनिया में अच्छाइयाँ, प्यार, भरोसा और एक दूसरे का सहारा हैं तो उसकी शुरुआत माँ के प्यार से होती हैं 💚❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Excited to present Mann Ki Baat Vol-1, a comic book by the Ministry of Culture (GoI) and Amar Chitra Katha, inspired by PM Modi’s radio program. 

Chapter 7 (Page 24) celebrates Pradeep Sangwan and Healing Himalayas’ journey of protecting the fragile Himalayan ecosystem through clean-up drives and sustainable initiatives. This recognition is a tribute to everyone who has supported and contributed to this mission. 

Together, we continue to strive for a cleaner, greener future. 🌿 #HealingHimalayas #Sustainability #MannKiBaat

latestPosts.caption:
We’re happy to announce that we’ll be heading to COP 29 to share our journey and mission with the global community! This incredible opportunity to represent Healing Himalayas on such a prominent platform would not be possible without the unwavering support of each volunteer, partner, and well-wisher who has contributed to our cause, whether directly or indirectly. 

We are deeply grateful for everyone who has stood by us, making it possible to bring our message to the world stage. Together, we’ll keep working toward a cleaner, sustainable future for the Himalayas and beyond.

 Thank you for believing in us!

#cop29 #healinghimalayas
